  • Constructor Details

    • WalkingFigure

      public WalkingFigure(MapWorld world, String color, boolean big, boolean loaded)
      Creates a new WalkingFigure that can roam the passed MapWorld. You can configure the look of the figure (if the corresponding images are available).
      Parameters:
      world - The world this figure walks on.
      color - The color of this figure. The lecture package contains "green" and "blue" variants.
      big - True if you want a bigger Version of the figure (the lecture package contains all colors in a big and a small version)
      loaded - True if you want to outfit your figure with a backpack (the lecture package contains all colors and sizes with and without a backpack)
      See Also:
      • WalkingFigure(MapWorld, String[])

  • Method Details

    • moveTo

      public void moveTo(double x, double y, double speed)
      Starts an animation that moves the figure from it's current position to the specified destination. Before you call moveTo, you should first call Sprite.clearAnimations() to make sure the animations do not overlap, otherwise you may get strange results. You can use Sprite.hasAnimations() to determine whether figure is still moving.

      When the figure reaches the destination it will call didFinishAnimation()

      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate in Pixels where the figure should move to
      y - The y-coordinate in Pixels where the figure should move to
      speed - The speed (in Pixels per Second) the figure should move
